sentences: Since 2017, he has hosted the weekly radio program The Boogie Down on WFUV.
He lived in Minneapolis before moving to New York City in 1996.
He adopted the stage name Binky Griptite in 1999.
In late 1997, he helped found the Brooklyn afrobeat ensemble Antibalas and played with them in their early years.
In late 1997, he helped found the Brooklyn afrobeat ensemble Antibalas and played with them in their early years.
Following the dissolution of Desco and the Soul Providers in 1999-2000, he formed The Dap-Kings with other former members as a band for Sharon Jones.
They recorded their debut album Dap Dippin' with Sharon Jones and the Dap-Kings in 2001.
In total, the group released seven studio album, concluding with 2017's Soul of a Woman.
Their 2014 album Give the People What They Want was nominated for the Grammy Award for Best R&B Album.
Following a twenty year tenure, Griptite departed from The Dap-Kings in September 2018.
Following a twenty year tenure, Griptite departed from The Dap-Kings in September 2018.
In addition to playing with the Dap-Kings, Binky has played on records for artists such as Janet Jackson and Amy Winehouse, with whom he toured extensively in 2007.
In July 2017, Griptite began hosting The Boogie Down on WFUV.
The all-vinyl radio show airs weekly on Saturday nights and highlights vintage soul and R&B tracks.

In July 2021, WFUV announced that Griptite and the station have amicably agreed to end the program, saying that Griptite hopes to revive the program at some future point, on a station or stations to be determined.
